China Fire & Security, LeMaitre, Pfizer: U.S. Equity Preview

-- B y   N i k o l a j   G a m m e l t o f t
-- 
2011-05-20T21:34:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-20/china-fire-security-lemaitre-vascular-pfizer-u-s-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in U.S. trading on May 23. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of 5:10 p.m. in  New York .  China Fire & Security Group Inc. (CFSG US) jumped 17
percent to $8.56. The Beijing-based maker of safety products is
being acquired by Bain Capital Partners LLC for $9 a share.  LeMaitre Vascular Inc. (LMAT)   lost 8.4 percent to $6.58.
The maker of medical devices for vascular surgeons said it is
closing a factory in California and exiting its aortic stent
graft business, and revising its 2011 revenue guidance to $61
million.  Pfizer Inc. (PFE)   climbed 0.2 percent to $20.73. The
world’s biggest drugmaker won U.S. regulatory approval to expand
marketing of a cancer drug for patients with the rare type of
pancreatic tumor diagnosed in  Apple Inc. (AAPL) ’s Steve Jobs
in 2004.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nikolaj Gammeltoft in New York at 
 ngammeltoft@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 